Turkey’s Cotton Imports to Climb Next Year, USDA Unit Says

-- B y   D e b a r a t i   R o y
-- 
2011-06-01T19:17:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/turkey-s-cotton-imports-to-climb-next-year-usda-unit-says.html
Turkey ’s cotton imports will climb to
3.672 million bales in the year starting Aug. 1 from an
estimated 3.442 million bales this season, according to unit of
the U.S. Department of Agriculture.  The USDA’s  Foreign Agricultural Service  posted the  report 
today on its website. A bale weighs 480 pounds or 218 kilograms.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Debarati Roy in New York at 
 droy5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net  